article.headline: Murray St. 85, SE Missouri 67
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. (AP) -- Bruce Carter and Danero Thomas both scored 16 points to lead Murray State over Southeast Missouri 85-67 Saturday. Murray State (9-11, 7-5 Ohio Valley Conference) took control of the game from the start, beginning with a 20-7 run in the first eight minutes of play. Although Southeast Missouri (8-14, 6-7) whittled the deficit to 20-13, that was as close as the Redhawks ever got the rest of the game. The Racers led 38-28 at the half and put the game awat on a 16-0 run five minutes into the second half, giving them a 50-36 lead. Southeast Missouri's poor shooting -- they shot 16-of-59 from the field and 7-of-33 from 3-point range -- kept them from making a run at Murray. Five technical fouls were called -- three on Southeast Missouri and two on Murray State. Ray George scored 15 points and Shawn Weatherspoon added 14 for the Racers. Brandon Foust scored 12 points and David Johnson contributed 11 for the Redhawks.
